sec.p:
Since a good filter needs to be tunable, this feature can be provided by filling the dielectric medium “air” with a nonlinear dielectric material (InGaAsP). InGaAsP is one of the most important premier Nonlinear Optical (NLO) materials because of its great chemical stability, high optical damage threshold, ease of obtaining in crystalline form, wide working ranges of wavelength and temperature, and conversion efficiency (Arivuoli 2001). The resonant wavelengths can be tuned without affecting the structure's outer size because the refractive index of the InGaAsP material is sensitive to the intensity of the incident light, generating a redshift for the resonance wavelengths. The equation of NLO material, εd for InGaAsP, can be written as (Kamari et al. 2021a, b):1εd=εL+χ(3)E2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
